text: Gyula Gömbös de Jákfa (26 December 1886 – 6 October 1936) was a Hungarian military officer and politician. He served as Prime Minister of Hungary from 1 October 1932 until his death on 6 October 1936. He was born in Murga, Austria- Hungary. Gömbös died in Munich, Germany from testicular cancer, aged 49. ==Other websites== Category:1886 births Category:1936 deaths Category:Cancer deaths in Germany Category:Deaths from testicular cancer Category:European military people Category:Prime ministers of Hungary
